Description: Fragment of perhaps double handle of an Egyptian pottery transport amphora, one barrel only preserved. Clay coarse red-brown; grey core. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 206, 26 Name Longinos; presumably a Hellenised Roman resident in Egypt.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1713)
